Stereotype.name: arrayvaluespecification
Stereotype.notes: Specifies the values for an array.

Tag.name: element
Tag.description: The value for a single array element. All ValueSpecifications aggregated by ArrayValueSpecification shall have the same structure.

Tag.name: intentedPartialInitializationCount
Tag.description:
This attribute shall only have a meaning for dynamic arrays and shall be taken as a sanity check: the number filled in the attribute shall be identical to the number of ArrayValueSpecification.element.
If the attribute does not exist it means that no partial initialization is intended.

Stereotype.name: compositevaluespecification
Stereotype.notes: This abstract meta-class acts a base class for ValueSpecifications that have a composite form.

Stereotype.name: constantspecification
Stereotype.notes: Specification of a constant that can be part of a package, i.e. it can be defined stand-alone.

Tag.name: valueSpec
Tag.description: Specification of an expression leading to a value for this constant.

Tag.name: applConstant
Tag.description: A ConstantSpecification defined in the application domain.

Tag.name: implConstant
Tag.description: A ConstantSpecification defined in the implementation domain.

Stereotype.name: numericalvaluespecification
Stereotype.notes: A numerical ValueSpecification which is intended to be assigned to a Primitive data element. Note that the numerical value is a variant, it can be computed by a formula.

Stereotype.name: recordvaluespecification
Stereotype.notes: Specifies the values for a record.

Tag.name: field
Tag.description: The value for a single record field. This could also be mapped explicitly to a record element of the data type using the shortName of the ValueSpecification. But this would introduce a relationship to the data type that is too strong. As of now, it is only important that the structure of the data type matches the structure of the Value Specification independently of the shortNames.

Stereotype.name: referencevaluespecification
Stereotype.notes: Specifies a reference to a data prototype to be used as an initial value for a pointer in the software.

Stereotype.name: textvaluespecification
Stereotype.notes: The purpose of TextValueSpecification is to define the labels that correspond to enumeration values.

Tag.name: value
Tag.description: This is the value itself. Note that vt uses the | operator to separate the values for the different bitfield masks in case that the semantics of the related DataPrototype is described by means of a BITFIELD_TEXTTABLE in the associated CompuMethod.

Stereotype.name: valuespecification
Stereotype.notes: Base class for expressions leading to a value which can be used to initialize a data object.
